in follows table follows_id field refers to all the users that a blogger is following and follows_userid refers to a particular blogger whose follows list is stored in the table.
if followers table, followers_id refers to all the users that are following a particular blogger and followers_userif refers to a particular blogger user followers list is stored in the table!
need to run "PRAGMA foreign key =ON;" to ensure that foreign key constraint is working
post_id sequence starts from 100


to be taken care of:
-> while inserting into comments table, make sure that the the post_id actually belongs the user_id mentioned for that comment
-> while inserting into follows or followers make sure they are different
-> while inserting in follows and followers make sure that the one being followed is an admin
to update in database while creating the database:
ON UPDATE CASCADE
